    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - MANIFOLDS - EXHAUST MANIFOLDS</stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>EXHAUST MANIFOLDS</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="3">
            <title>REMOVAL</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">Left Exhaust Manifold</emph>
                    - Remove eight prevailing torque bolts and hardened washers,
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350204">2.4</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    . Remove the manifold and gasket.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prior to removal of right exhaust manifold, remove the oil level gauge assembly as
                    follows:
                </para>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Loosen the nut and washer from the stud bolt, to free the oil level gauge tube
                        bracket. Refer to
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350205">2.5</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        .
                    </para>
                </step2>
                <step2>
                    <para count="1">Remove the oil level gauge tube assembly (with bracket) from the crankcase (
                        <emph type="bold">Figure
                            <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350206">2.6</hotlnk>
                        </emph>
                        ).
                    </para>
                    <figure id="ef4350204" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg14563" filename="../figcg1/CG14563.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.4 Removal - Left Exhaust Manifold</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4350205" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg12319" filename="../figcg1/CG12319.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.5 Loosen Oil Level Gauge Bracket</caption>
                    </figure>
                    <figure id="ef4350206" figsize="col-wide">
                        <graphic id="cg12320" filename="../figcg1/CG12320.webp" type="webp"/>
                        <caption>Figure 2.6 Remove Oil Level Gauge Assembly</caption>
                    </figure>
                </step2>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">Right Exhaust Manifold</emph>
                    - Remove the seven prevailing torque bolts, one prevailing torque stud bolt and eight hardened
                    washers (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e435_23.xml" xrefid="ef4350207">2.7</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
